*****
[2]
Date: Wed 3 Aug 2011
Source: Associated Press [edited]
http://www2.wjtv.com/news/2011/aug/03/8-confirmed-sick-from-milk-at-western-pa-dairy-ar-2224844/


State health officials say 8 people have now been confirmed to be
sickened by drinking bacteria-tainted milk from a western Pennsylvania
dairy. Officials with the Brunton Dairy in Aliquippa have said they're
cooperating with the Pennsylvania Department of Health investigation.

Health officials updated The Associated Press on Wed 3 Aug 2011,
saying the number of people sickened so far by the _Yersinia
enterocolitica_ is now 8. The illnesses 1st began to be reported last
week.

The dairy about 25 miles northwest of Pittsburgh is certified to
pasteurize milk, but has temporarily stopped production.

